==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[chimera]],'' from the Latin ''[[chimaera]],'' from the {{Gr.}} (''chimaira''), which means ''she-goat.'' This term entered English around 1638.
===Adjective=== (adv. [[chimerically]])
'''chimerical'''
# A figment of the imagination; [[fantastic]] (in the [[archaic]] sense).
# Inherently fantastic.

